In article <1993Oct7.080908.27638@uwasa.fi> hensel@garbo.uwasa.fi (Mike Hensel) writes:

   i wonder if there is a (easy) way to modify pgp source to allow keys larger
   than 1024 bits. once i asked phillip zimmermann about it but i never got any
   reply except an auto message.

1st: This should really be on alt.security.pgp, not on sci.crypt.

To answer your question:  you can modify your copy of PGP to use bigger
keys, but no one else on the planet will be able to use it.  Basically,
no keys bigger than 1024 bits is currently supported, so use at your own
risk.

-derek
